==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Birds-foot
<hw>Bird's"-foot`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A papilionaceous plant, the <spn>Ornithopus</spn>, having a curved,
cylindrical pod tipped with a short, clawlike point.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bird's-foot trefoil</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <cd>A genus of plants (<gen>Lotus</gen>) with clawlike
pods. <spn>Lotus corniculatas</spn>, with yellow flowers, is very common
in Great Britain.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>the related plant,
<spn>Trigonella ornithopodioides</spn>, is also European.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bird's-mouth</ent>⟦br⟧
